</p>
<h2>
    Tides and Timing: Best Time of Day to Catch Pink Salmon
</h2>
<p>
    Timing is everything in salmon fishing.
</p>
<h3>
    Morning vs. Evening Bite Patterns
</h3>
<ul>
    <li>
        Early morning (5–9 a.m.) is the most active period.
    </li>
    <li>
        Evening fishing, especially near dusk, can also produce excellent results.
    </li>
</ul>
<h3>
    Ideal Tide Conditions
</h3>
<p>
    For rivers affected by tides, like the Columbia, fish during the <strong>incoming tide</strong> or just before <strong>high tide</strong> for best success.
</p>
